# PIKO COMMAND - Environment Variables Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and configure as needed

# ======================================
# CURRENT STATUS: OAuth NOT Implemented
# ======================================
# PIKO COMMAND uses browser intents for social media posting
# OAuth credentials below are OPTIONAL and not currently used
# The app works perfectly without these variables
# ======================================

# Twitter/X OAuth 2.0 Credentials (OPTIONAL - Not Used)
# Get from: https://developer.twitter.com/en/portal/dashboard
VITE_TWITTER_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_TWITTER_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Instagram OAuth Credentials (OPTIONAL - Not Used)
# Get from: https://developers.facebook.com/
VITE_INSTAGRAM_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_INSTAGRAM_CLIENT_SECRET=

# TikTok OAuth Credentials (OPTIONAL - Not Used)
# Get from: https://developers.tiktok.com/
VITE_TIKTOK_CLIENT_KEY=
VITE_TIKTOK_CLIENT_SECRET=

# Facebook OAuth Credentials (OPTIONAL - Not Used)
# Get from: https://developers.facebook.com/
VITE_FACEBOOK_APP_ID=
VITE_FACEBOOK_APP_SECRET=

# LinkedIn OAuth Credentials (OPTIONAL - Not Used)
# Get from: https://www.linkedin.com/developers/
VITE_LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID=
VITE_LINKEDIN_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ======================================
# WHAT YOU ACTUALLY NEED
# ======================================
# 1. GitHub Personal Access Token (PAT)
#    - Configure in: THE VAULT > GitHub Storage
#    - Requires: repo scope
#    - Format: ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
#
# 2. YouTube Data API Key (OPTIONAL)
#    - Configure in: YouTube Vault settings
#    - Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#    - Enables: Real video fetching from YouTube channel
#
# Both credentials are configured in-app, not via environment variables
# This provides better security and user control
# ======================================

# Important Security Notes:
# 1. Never commit the actual .env file with real credentials to version control
# 2. All sensitive credentials are stored securely in browser localStorage
# 3. GitHub tokens and YouTube API keys are validated before use
# 4. See SECURITY_IMPROVEMENTS.md for more security details

